<h1><span class="namespace" title="namespace std">std::</span><a href="/reference/string/string/">string</a>::npos</h1>
<div class="C_prototype"><pre>static const size_t npos = -1;</pre></div><div id="I_description">Maximum value for size_t</div>
<section id="description">
<tt>npos</tt> is a static member constant value with the greatest possible value for an element of type <a href="/size_t">size_t</a>.<br>
<br>
This value, when used as the value for a <i>len</i> (or <i>sublen</i>) parameter in <a href="/string">string</a>'s member functions, means <i>"until the end of the string"</i>.<br>
<br>
As a return value, it is usually used to indicate no matches.<br>
<br>
This constant is defined with a value of <tt>-1</tt>, which because <a href="/size_t">size_t</a> is an unsigned integral type, it is the largest possible representable value for this type.<br>
